issue.title: Are there any Table plugins that display correctly?
issue.body:
I went through the 3/4 plugins available for creating tables and they all have similar issues, where the drop-down options don't display any text. Does anyone know a way to get table input in a way that works as expected?

Sorry if this is the wrong avenue for this questions, just trying to get an instance working for some collaborative work.

issue.title: Broken links on etherpad.org
issue.body:
<!-- IMPORTANT: Please disable plugins prior to posting a bug report.  If you have a problem with a plugin please post on the plugin repository.  Thanks! -->

**Describe the bug**
There are many broken links on the etherpad.org website.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Go to https://etherpad.org/
2. Scroll down to headings `Collaborating in really real-time` and `Contribute`
3. Click on **pick** and **get in touch** respectively
4. See error (screenshots attached)

**Expected behavior**
The link should take the user to a valid page on the etherpad.org website.

**Screenshots**

![nw](https://github.com/ether/etherpad-lite/assets/42183055/89d76c34-8ec5-4ec9-b60d-fc7007cae078)
![nww](https://github.com/ether/etherpad-lite/assets/42183055/d9c64ba8-3b76-40ab-86c0-b55006ba4a64)
![getit](https://github.com/ether/etherpad-lite/assets/42183055/1bc6fea4-913a-4e31-924d-a0f3f8996d4d)

**Server (please complete the following information):**
 - Etherpad version: not required
 - OS: [not required]
 - Node.js version (`node --version`): not required
 - npm version (`npm --version`): not required
 - Is the server free of plugins: not required

**Desktop (please complete the following information):**
 - OS: [Windows 10]
 - Browser [Brave]
 - Version [Chromium 118]

**Smartphone (please complete the following information):**
 - Device: [Xiomi Note 5]
 - OS: [android 9]
 - Browser [Brave]
 - Version [118]

**Additional context**
Everything else is working fine.

issue.title: Plugin to obey prefers-color-scheme?
issue.body:
* * *

name: Plugin request
about: Suggest a plugin for this project
title: 'ep_prefer_theme'
labels: plugin request
assignees: 

* * *

**Is your plugin request related to a problem? Please describe.**
We received a request about configuring dark mode on Etherpad for Sandstorm. I see there are dark skinVariant selections for Etherpad, but I am unsure how to invoke them. I saw there is an ep_solar plugin which changes the theme based on the position of the sun, but not one that changes based on your preference.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
I think it'd be ideal if Etherpad obeyed prefers-color-scheme provided by the web browser. While I feel like this is a good default behavior, it would perhaps be best implemented as a plugin.

comment.body: @ocdtrekkie Thanks for the issue. I added a plugin for that https://www.npmjs.com/package/ep_prefer_color_scheme . I don't know what your requirements are. The themes are currently hardcoded. If you want to have that configurable please let me know.
